{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Grease a baking tin (30 cm x 24 cm x 6 cm) then set aside. Place flour, milk, ground mixed spice, salt, yeast, sugar and egg in mixing bowl then mix <b>20 sec\/37°C\/speed 3<b>. Knead <b>3 min\/<b> then leave dough in mixing bowl until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours).","After this time, knead <b>30 sec\/<b> then transfer dough to a well-floured surface (dough will be sticky and very soft). Sprinkle with flour then roll into a rectangle (approx. 30 cm x 50 cm) using a flour-dusted rolling pin."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Spread 50 g soft butter over dough with a soft spatula. Fold bottom third up to cover middle third and top third down over this. Give dough a quarter turn so that the fold is on the left and roll out again into a rectangle, then fold into three again.","Roll into a rectangle (approx. 30 cm x 50 cm), adding flour to surface as required to stop dough sticking. Spread sugar, currants and mixed spice over dough. Roll up into a sausage shape then cut into 12 equal slices.","Place slices cut side up, about ½ cm apart, in prepared tin. Cover with cling film and leave to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour). Towards the end of proving time, preheat oven to 200°C.","Bake for 25-30 minutes (200°C). Allow buns to rest in tin while making drizzle."]},{"title":"Drizzle","content":["Place a small bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in icing sugar. Remove bowl and add water 1 tsp at a time to make a thin icing.","Drizzle over buns while still warm then remove from tin and serve warm or at room temperature."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["unsalted butter, for greasing","400 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","220 g milk","1 tsp ground mixed spice","3 tsp fine sea salt","2 tsp dried instant yeast","2 Tbsp caster sugar","1 medium egg"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["50 g unsalted butter, soft","50 g caster sugar","75 g currants","½ tsp ground mixed spice"]},{"title":"Drizzle","content":["50 g icing sugar","water, to mix"]}],"id":"r82531","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-ubcI9otVq60\/XZWqNeeVTfI\/AAAAAAAAfUo\/Bvm6IvpIQnYjGCtUVvJggzSHh9gFBRsXACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FTLipzu3skjR-GQV.png","title":"Chelsea Buns","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.3 g","fat":"4.7 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"39.8 g","calories":"932 kJ \/ 223 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tin (30 cm x 24 cm x 6 cm), rolling pin, soft spatula, cling film, small bowl, pastry brush, oven, oven","basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 30m","12 pieces"]}